Add explicit `load()` for `cc_library` to upstream `core/BUILD.bazel`.

The BCR module `prometheus-cpp@1.3.0.bcr.2` is unmodified upstream
(only `MODULE.bazel` is patched by the BCR repack) and still uses bare
`cc_library(...)` without a `load("@rules_cc//cc:defs.bzl", "cc_library")`.
Bazel 9 removed the legacy global `cc_library` symbol, so analysis fails
with "rule has been removed". The one-line `load()` here un-breaks the
upstream BUILD without touching project-wide rule discipline. Drop this
patch when prometheus-cpp publishes a Bazel-9-clean BCR rev (track at
https://github.com/jupp0r/prometheus-cpp).

--- a/core/BUILD.bazel
+++ b/core/BUILD.bazel
@@ -1,4 +1,5 @@
 load("//bazel:export_header.bzl", "generate_dummy_export_header")
+load("@rules_cc//cc:defs.bzl", "cc_library")

 generate_dummy_export_header(
     name = "export_header",
